Thanks Ainwein. Its a good thing to hear people talking good about your guild when you are not even friends with them (I don't recall ever having met you in game). <br>
<br>
Guilds I would recommend are...<br>
<br>
Vision (heh, seriously <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ), but they are not recruiting as far as I know, and even if so, you gotta be around lvl58-60 if I am right. <br>
<br>
Ordre des Corsaires, lead by Photonette. But they're french.<br>
<br>
Amalgam of Force, lead by Danadiele and Palimax. They are not just lvl46+, they have a lot of lower lvls too.<br>
<br>
Valiant Crusaders, not sure about their Guildleaders name. But Kanyli and Kadath are officers, that may help. They also have a lot of people under lvl46 tho.<br>
<br>
Exiled Aliance. I don't know their guildleader by heart. But I always just heared good things about them, and those few occasions I had to do with em proved the rumors right.<br>
<br>
<br>
If you're looking for a guild and are considering one of the mentioned guilds, the Legend of the Jokers have a level requirement of lvl50 now. We are not looking for special classes since we value the attitude and the person behind the char when we choose new members, not their class.<br>
