Phantasmist of CoFE<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/udammur.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dammur</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/6/02 2:38:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=352.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://64.77.120.194/Dammur1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gr8 Guilds of A-Ro</span><hr size=1> Your best bet, looking for a guild at 46 + is probabilly going to be one of the ones that were mentioned already.  Look for one that is in it's planeiar days or early to mid kael days, which is more &quot;family oriented&quot;.  You want a family oriented guild over a loot oriented guild (depending on your personality).  <br>
Family oriented guilds are harder to get into and become a full fledged member, but they provide a much better environment to play in, and have a greater tendency to stick together throughout time.  <br>
Their is a large tendancy for loot oriented guilds to fall apart...someoen gets too greedy, people complain about loot, [undue] favortism occours, etc.  Even though loot oriented guilds are easier to get into, they are much less rewarding in the long run.  <br>
The tendency for loot oriented guilds to fall apart may be a byproduct of overrecruitment.  If you, as a guild, are strong...but you recruit 2 or 3 bad apples, that are not a good fit, are loot hungry, etc, it can tear the best guilds apart.  Just booting the individual in question is often not a solution, because that individual may have made a few friends in the guild before the boot, and may cause other people to leave with him.  If the wrong person leaves a guild, it can also cause a rift big enough for a guild to fall apart.  This [i hope] goes to explain why you will find recruitment so hard in a family oriented guild...because they realize this fact.<br>
<br>
<br>
In order to get in a guild that curently does tov, or higher end luclin zones, you will need to be 55 + at a bare minimum...many tov guilds are closed to all new recruitment unless you fall in the one or two classes that they are short on, or are a very good real life friend with one of their members, and even then, you can come accross very high (58 + or even 60 only) level requirements.  Most of these guilds, if they are successful, will be &quot;family oriented&quot; as well.  The loot oriented guilds just do not stand the test of time.<br>
<br>
